      • unconsumedTokensShouldBe

        private void unconsumedTokensShouldBe(java.lang.String expectedTokens)
        The "isX" Parser methods try to recognize an X at the beginning of the input, but should not consume tokens after the X. For example, a factor may contain multiplications but not additions, so given a string such as "3*x+5*y", the isFactor method should consume and accept the "3*x" but leave the "+5*y" for later.

        This method tests the input string to see whether the correct tokens are left unconsumed.

        Parameters:
        expectedTokens - The following Tokens that should remain in the input string after the X has been consumed.
